<paragraph blockId="30.[192,1440,1744,1929]" lastBlockId="31.[192,1440,1444,1596]" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,1744,1768]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Definition.</emphasis>
A likely sister to 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1955" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1955" box="[554,794,1744,1768]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Misius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[554,636,1744,1767]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Misius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[644,794,1744,1768]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[809,863,1744,1768]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">type</typeStatus>
and the only species 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1891" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="misius">
<emphasis box="[1123,1333,1744,1768]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Pamphila misius</emphasis>
Mabille, 1891
</taxonomicName>
), this genus is removed from 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, 1900" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[594,898,1776,1800]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Parphorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[594,721,1776,1800]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Parphorus</emphasis>
Godman, 1900
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[912,965,1776,1800]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1891" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1891" box="[1059,1427,1776,1800]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Phlebodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="storax">
<emphasis box="[1059,1257,1776,1800]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Phlebodes storax</emphasis>
Mabille, 1891
</taxonomicName>
), where it was placed previously (
<figureCitation box="[587,720,1808,1832]" captionStart-0="Figure 11" captionStart-1="Figure 12" captionStartId-0="29.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionStartId-1="31.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox-0="[195,1438,214,1295]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1440,214,1295]" captionTargetId-0="figure@29.[194,1442,213,1296]" captionTargetId-1="figure@31.[192,1440,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId-0="29" captionTargetPageId-1="31" captionText-0="Figure 11. Nuclear genome and Z chromosome trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." captionText-1="Figure 12. Mitochondrial genome and COI barcode trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677257" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677259" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3677257/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3677259/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Fig. 11â€“12</figureCitation>
). Keys to J.34.9 or J.34.10a in 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[1098,1263,1808,1832]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans (1955)</bibRefCitation>
. Diagnosed by long and prominent triangular hyaline yellow spot filling out forewing cell R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1113,1122,1855,1869]" fontSize="6" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">5</subScript>
-M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1155,1164,1855,1869]" fontSize="6" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">1</subScript>
from the base to about a third of its length (except 
<taxonomicName authority="E. Bell, 1947" authorityName="E. Bell" authorityYear="1947" box="[537,816,1872,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Vorates" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paramus">
<emphasis box="[537,646,1873,1896]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">paramus</emphasis>
E. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bell" box="[689,816,1872,1896]" firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref26696" refString="Bell, E. L. 1947. A new genus and some new species and subspecies of neotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). American Museum Novitates 1354: 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1947">Bell, 1947</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which has typical for the genus genitalia), and no other apical forewing hyaline spots, hindwing below with more or less prominent pale ray along vein M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[217,226,1459,1473]" fontSize="6" pageId="31" pageNumber="30">1</subScript>
from wing base to outer margin. Genitalia differ from relatives by a combination of the following characters: uncus twice as long as tegumen, arms parallel and narrow, gnathos vestigial, valva twice as long as wide, harpe not extending much beyond bulky rounded ampulla, upturned and not separated from ampulla. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly536.116.6:A107G, aly 
<date box="[228,352,1572,1596]" pageId="31" pageNumber="30" value="2124-04-17">2124.4.17</date>
:G268T, aly6377.1.2:A4462G, aly208.50.8:T236A, aly536.108.1:C2126T.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
